<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>PvP Races and Warriors</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?TheRealmWeaver">TheRealmWeaver</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 10:29 a.m. 15/4/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> PvP Races and Warriors<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=1910" TARGET=_self>WHATS BEST CLASS/RACE FOR PVP</A> (Valdrain)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>First off, if you want to be a warrior, be a Troll or an Ogre, hands down. All faction considerations aside, being a warrior of any other race will only leave you envying those people with the patience to deal with the way NPCs react to Trolls and Ogres. They will have a load more hitpoints than you, they will hit harder, they will be able to carry more weight ( a very important consideration of you ever plan on wearing plate armor ), and they get a natural slam attack. Don't forget that Troll and Ogre warriors are given the opportunity to improve their faction. Others races NEVER have the opportunity to match Ogres and Trolls in strength or stamina.

<BR>Secondly, Petunia is right, the PvP server is not about who can take whom in a one-on-one battle. The PvP will most often take the form of large battles, city raids, race wars, guild fights, gang violence, or riots. Your usefullness in a group is VERY important to PvP and, contrary to your belief, Bards are one of the most coveted classes on Rallos Zek for their contribution to group PvP.
<BR>If you're looking for one race that will make you some kind of powerhouse, then you will never find it. Wizards at max level can kill in two spells, and Warriors at max level can take down a spellcaster in two rounds. It's a matter of taste.
<P>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
